caption: I was pleased to see this restaurant offer so many vegan menu items. First off, I would recommend not getting the vegan broccoli beef—it wasn’t bad it just wasn’t good. The spring roles were meh. And the volcano spare ribs were lit (literally, on fire)—fun in presentation and flavor. The staff were super hard working and very attentive, high marks for service.  TW if it bothers you to see marine animals kept in crowded tanks with dirty water, avoid avoid.

Super tasty food, convenient parking, and fantastic service - we were welcomed in for a take-out order even after closing! Totally not expected, but much appreciated.  Everything was delicious and reasonably priced.

“Taste” is everything with me and my family, and the food at this place was absolutely amazing  and delicious!! And to top it off, the prices were extremely reasonable. I actually had to look at my bill twice! The owner Kana was very cordial and would continually check on us. Wow! Loved everything about it!!
The salt and pepper squid was pretty good
My wife enjoyed the seafood options

I really love this place. Chinese food can definitely be hit or miss. But Mini Garden doesn't disappoint my family. We love the owner Kana and the things we eat, we really love. Their dessert which is complimentary is a lovely ending to the meal.

They have an extensive menu with many vegetarian options. There were many locals there in their COVID compliant dining room. We were picking up only one dish and ran into a neighborhood local who raved about the place. The service was extremely quick and the Salt and Pepper Tofu was delicious! Judging by the crowd of what appeared to be regulars, the reviews on the wall and the yummy dish we sampled...we were fortunate to find Mini Garden.
Good place to eat and have your parties. They do their best all the time.

Owners are super friendly food was great she helped me with my order for my mother's 80th birthday. Everyone just loved the food especially the duck and fried rice dishes we ordered. She took special care packing the order since i had to pick it up early that day for dinner later that night...thanks so much

One of my all-time favorite restaurants to dine in or get take out. The food is always great quality and delicious. There are also hearty vegetarian options, and the food stays true to fine Chinese dining. The service is also fantastic as all the employees are well mannered, and they always offer free dessert when dining in.

Decent place for better than okay Chinese food.  We ordered vegetarian dishes that used some kind of meat substitute.  It was not the best or the worse but better than okay.  The portions we're good sized.  The staff is pleasant,  the service was fairly quick but the restaurant was not busy so this helped.  The restaurant has parking and appeared to be clean.  The best dishes I had were the eggplant and the green beans.  The strangest was the substituted fish like dish.  I'm unsure if I would come back again and I don't think I would recommend it unless the people I am with are strictly vegetarian and they wanted to try it out.  I have no issues with MSG so don't know and don't care if it's used.  Overall we had a good dinning experience and the food was better than okay.

This place is horrible. Do not order food from this restaurant. Stay away from this place. Order through Uber eat...the noodle and the duck was not fresh. Throw away two food boxes. Their vegetables is very odd and chewy especially the choy some .

One of my fav Chinese food restaurants in Honolulu.  Food is always consistently good and portions are ample. Never ordered a dish we didn't like. A lunchtime fav is the stewed noodle plate with 2 choices,and I always take the roast duck and ginger onion chicken.
Very nice Chinese restaurant

If you like real Chinese food you need to eat here. This little hole in the wall is a hidden gem. We recently spent a week in Honolulu and what we ate at Mini Garden was THE BEST meal we had the entire trip (and we ate at Morimoto and Stage). This is not the super Americanized "Chinese" food that must mainlanders are used to, but it's not intimidating either. Anyone can find something they like here. The ginger fish and char su pork were AMAZING! We loved the salt and pepper tofu and the duck too. Go with a big group and eat family style so you can try everything.
Great authentic Chinese food.
I like to eat there.
The wait staff always welcome us with a smile. When we want to try something different, a suggestion is always provided, which is never wrong. We thoroughly enjoy eating here.
